{"parse":{"title":"student","pageid":47667,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Student|stúdent|stüdent|študent|Študent}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|en|ine-pro|*(s)tewd-}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|student}}, {{m|enm|studient}}, from {{der|en|fro|estudiant}}, {{m|fro|estudiente}}, from {{der|en|la|studēns}}, present participle of {{m|la|studeō|t=dedicate oneself to, study}}. Equivalent to {{af|en|study|-ent}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈstjuː.dn̩t/}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈst͡ʃuː.dn̩t/|a=yod-coalescence}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈstu.dn̩t/|a=yod-dropping}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈstɪʊ.dənt/|a=Canada,dialectal}}\n* {{hyph|en|stu|dent}}\n* {{audio|en|En-uk-student.ogg|a=UK}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-student.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-student.wav|a=Southern England}}\n* {{rhymes|en|uːdənt|s=2}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# A [[person]] who [[study|studies]] or [[learn]]s about a particular [[subject]].\n#: {{syn|en|candlewaster|scholar|devotee|disciple}}\n#: {{ux|en|She is a '''student''' of human interactions.}}\n#: {{ux|en|He is a '''student''' of life.}}\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Twelfth Night|IV|ii|271|1|I am not tall enough to become the function well, nor leane enough to bee thought a good '''Studient''' : but to be ſaid an honeſt man and a good houſkeeper goes as fairely, as to ſay, a carefull man, & a great ſcholler. The Competitors enter.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Seashore Plants of Southern Califonria|passage=The '''student''' of marine life in Southern California should become aware that {{...}} a great many changes have taken place during the past century that have modified the characters of the plant and animal communities of the seashore.|year=1966|author=E. Yale Dawson|page=6|isbn=0520003004|year_published=1975|lccn=66-19103|publisher=University of California Press|edition_plain=3rd printing|location=Berkley|pageurl=https://www.google.com/books/edition/Seashore_Plants_of_Southern_California/b_bBAqehDCMC?gbpv=1&pg=PA6}}\n# A person who is formally [[enrolled]] at a [[school]], a [[college]] or [[university]], or another educational institution.\n#: {{ux|en|The '''students''' were out raising funds for [[rag week]].}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=a. 1774|author=w:Oliver Goldsmith|chapter=Essay XII|title=The Miscellaneous Works of Dr. Goldsmith|volume=III|location=Edinburgh|publisher=Geo. Mudie|year_published=1792|page=71|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=7ykvAAAAYAAJ&pg=RA1-PA71|passage=In general, alſo, it may be obſerved, that a greater degree of gentility is affixed to the character of a '''ſtudent''' in England than elſewhere ; by which means our clergy have an opportunity of ſeeing better company while young, and of ſooner wearing off thoſe prejudices which they are apt to imbibe even in the beſt regulated univerſities, and which may be juſtly termed the vulgar errors of the wiſe.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1868|author=Charles Haight Farnham|quotee=w:Francis Parkman|title=Autobiography|quoted_in=“Spiritual Growth”, in ''A Life of Francis Parkman''|location=Toronto|publisher=George N. Morang and Company|year_published=1900|page=321|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=ktQvAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA321|passage=In behalf of manhood and common sense, he would protest against such a conclusion ; and if any pale '''student,''' glued to his desk here, seek an apology for a way of life whose natural fruit is that pallid and emasculate scholarship of which New England has had too many examples, it will be far better that this sketch had not been written.}}\n#* {{quote-book\n|en\n|year=1971\n|author=w:Lyndon Johnson\n|title=w:The Vantage Point\n|url=https://archive.org/details/vantagepointpers00john/\n|publisher=w:Holt, Reinhart & Winston\n|ISBN=0-03-084492-4\n|LCCN=74-102146\n|OCLC=1067880747\n|page=180\n|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/vantagepointpers00john/page/180/\n|text=A handful of young '''students''' bent on showing their patriotism had stirred up more trouble than they possibly could have imagined.}}\n## {{lb|en|in particular}} A person who is enrolled at a [[college]] or [[university]] {{q|as contrasted with a [[pupil]] or [[schoolchild]] attending a [[primary school|primary]] or [[secondary school]]}}.\n\n====Antonyms====\n* {{l|en|teacher}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|antistudent|cyberstudent|multistudent|nonstudent|studency|studentese|studentess|studentification|studentization|studentized|studentizing|studentlike|studentry|studentship\n|A student|non-traditional student|nontraditional student|student driver|traditional student\n|studenthood\n|studential\n|studentish\n|studentless|student nation\n|studently|student affairs\n|studenty|student lamp\n|art student|exchange student|grad student|graduate student|graduate student descent|honor student|international student|legacy student|mature student|mature-age student|medical student|antistudent|cyberstudent|multistudent|nonstudent|studency|studentese|studentess|studentification|studentization|studentized|studentizing|studentlike|studentry|studentship|mud student|parent-teacher-student association|primary school student|professional student|student body|student council|student ghetto|student hour|student loan|student number|student strike|student syndrome|student teacher|student union|student voice|tertiary student|transfer student|student-athlete}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|person who studies a subject}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Afar: {{tt|aa|barteyna}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|student}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|nxënës|m}}, {{tt+|sq|nxënëse|f}}, {{tt+|sq|student|m}}, {{tt+|sq|studente|f}}\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{tt|alt|ӱренчик}}\n* Amharic: {{tt|am|ተማሪ|m|f}}\n* Arabic: {{tt+|ar|طَالِب|m}}, {{tt|ar|طَالِبَة|f}}, {{tt|ar|تِلْمِيذ|m}}, {{tt|ar|تِلْمِيذَة|f}}, {{t|ar|طَالِب عِلْم|m}}, {{t|ar|طَالِبَة عِلْم|f|tr=ṭālibat ʕilm}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{tt|arz|طالب|m|tr=ṭāleb}}, {{tt|arz|طالبة|f|tr=ṭāleba}}\n*: South Levantine Arabic: {{tt|ajp|طالب|m|tr=ṭāleb}}, {{tt|ajp|تلميذ|f|tr=tilmīz}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|ուսանող}}, {{tt+|hy|ստուդենտ}}\n* Assamese: {{tt|as|ছাত্ৰ}} {{q|male}}, {{tt|as|ছাত্ৰী}} {{q|female}}, {{tt|as|ছাত্ৰ-ছাত্ৰী}}\n* Asturian: {{tt+|ast|estudiante|m|f}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|tələbə}}\n* Basque: {{tt|eu|ikasle}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|студэ́нт|m}}, {{tt|be|студэ́нтка|f}}\n* Bengali: {{tt+|bn|ছাত্র}}, {{tt+|bn|তালিব}}, {{tt+|bn|শাগরেদ}}\n* Bole: {{tt|bol|pukara}}\n* Breton: {{t+|br|studier}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt|bg|студе́нт|m}}, {{tt|bg|студе́нтка|f}}\n* Burmese: {{tt+|my|ကျောင်းသား}}, {{tt+|my|ကျောင်းသူ}} {{qualifier|female}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|estudiant|m|f}}\n* Cherokee: {{tt|chr|ᏗᏕᏠᏆᏍᎩ}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{tt|yue|學生|tr=hok6 saang1, hok6 sang1}}\n*: Dungan: {{tt|dng|щүәсын}}\n*: Eastern Min: {{t|cdo|學生}}\n*: Hakka: {{t|hak|學生|tr=ho̍k-sâng}}\n*: Hokkien: {{tt+|nan-hbl|學生|tr=ha̍k-seng}}\n*: Jin: {{t|cjy|學生}}\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|學生}}\n*: Wu: {{tt|wuu|學生}}\n* Cornish: {{tt|kw|studhyor|m}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|student|m}}, {{tt+|cs|studentka|f}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|studerende|c}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|student|m}}, {{tt+|nl|studente|f}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|lernanto}}\n* Estonian: {{tt|et|üliõpilane}}, {{tt|et|tudeng}}, {{tt|et|õpilane}}, {{tt-check|et|õppija}}\n* Faroese: {{tt|fo|lesandi|m}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|opiskelija}}, {{tt+|fi|tutkija}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|étudiant|m}}, {{tt+|fr|étudiante|f}}, {{tt+|fr|élève|m|f}}\n* Galician: {{tt|gl|estudante|m|f}}\n* Georgian: {{tt|ka|მოსწავლე}}, {{tt|ka|სტუდენტი}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Student|m}}, {{tt+|de|Studentin|f}}; {{tt+|de|Lernender|m}} {{tt+|de|Lernende|f}}\n* Gothic: {{tt|got|𐍃𐌹𐍀𐍉𐌽𐌴𐌹𐍃|m}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|μαθητής|m}}, {{tt+|el|μαθήτρια|f}}, {{tt+|el|σπουδαστής|m}}, {{tt+|el|σπουδάστρια|f}}, {{tt+check|el|μελετητής|m}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{tt|grc|μαθητής|m}}, {{tt|grc|μαθήτρια|f}}\n* Guarani:\n*: Paraguayan Guarani: {{tt-check|gug|temimbo'e}}\n* Gujarati: {{tt|gu|વિદ્યાર્થી|m}}\n* Hausa: {{tt+|ha|ɗalibi}}\n* Hawaiian: {{tt|haw|haumāna}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|סְטוּדֶנְט|m|tr=studént}},