 {{tt|mnc|ᡨᠠᠴᡳᠰᡳ}}, {{tt|mnc|ᡧᠠᠪᡳ}}\n* Māori: {{tt|mi|ākonga}}\n* Maranao: {{tt|mrw|morit}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|विद्यार्थी|m}}, {{t|mr|विद्यार्थिनी|f}}\n* Mingrelian: {{tt|xmf|მოგურაფუ}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt+|mn|оюутан}}, {{tt+|mn|сурагч}}\n*: Mongolian script: {{tt|mn|ᠣᠶᠤᠲᠠᠨ}}, {{tt|mn|ᠰᠤᠷᠤᠭᠴᠢ}}\n* Navajo: {{tt|nv|ółtaʼí}}\n* Nepali: {{tt|ne|विद्यार्थी}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt|nb|student|m}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{tt+|nn|student|m}}\n* Occitan: {{tt+|oc|estudiant|m}}\n* Odia: {{tt+|or|ଛାତ୍ର}}, {{tt+|or|ଚାଟ}}\n* Old English: {{tt|ang|leornere|m}}\n* Old Saxon: {{tt-check|osx|giungaro|m}}, {{tt|osx|jungaro|m}}\n* Pannonian Rusyn: {{t|rsk|студент|m}}, {{t|rsk|студентка|f}}\n* Pashto: {{tt+|ps|محصل|m|tr=mohasel}}, {{tt|ps|محصله|f|tr=mohasela}}, {{tt+|ps|طالب|m|tr=tāleb}}\n* Persian:\n*: Dari: {{tt|prs|مُحَصِّل}}, {{t|prs|طَالِب}}\n*: Iranian Persian: {{tt|fa-ira|دانِشْجو}}, {{tt|fa-ira|طالِب}}, {{tt|fa-ira|طالِبِ عِلْم}} {{q|lofty}}, {{tt|fa-ira|شاگِرْد}}, {{tt|fa-ira|دانِش‌آموز}}, {{t|fa-ira|تِلْمیذ}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{tt|pdt|Scheela|m}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|student|m}}, {{tt+|pl|studentka|f}}, {{tt+|pl|uczeń|m}}, {{tt+|pl|uczennica|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|estudante|m|f}}, {{tt+|pt|aluno|m}}, {{tt+|pt|aluna|f}}, {{tt+|pt|estudioso|m}}, {{tt+|pt|estudiosa|f}}\n* Punjabi: {{t-needed|pa}}\n* Quechua: {{tt+|qu|yachakuq}}\n* Romagnol: {{tt|rgn|alév|m}}, {{tt|rgn|aliév|m}}\n* Romani: {{tt|rom|siklǒvno|m}}, {{tt|rom|siklǒvni|f}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|student|m}}, {{tt+|ro|studentă|f}}\n* Romansh: {{tt|rm|student|m}}, {{tt|rm|studenta|f}} {{q|Rumantsch Grischun, Surmiran, Puter, Vallader}}, {{tt|rm|studentessa|f}} {{q|Rumantsch Grischun, Sursilvan, Sutsilvan}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|студе́нт|m}}, {{tt+|ru|студе́нтка|f}}, {{tt+|ru|уча́щийся|m}}, {{tt+|ru|уча́щаяся|f}}\n* Sanskrit: {{tt+|sa|शिष्य|m|f}}, {{tt+|sa|छात्त्र|m}}, {{tt+|sa|विद्यार्थिन्|m}}, {{tt-check|sa|छात्त्रा|f}}\n* Scots: {{tt|sco|collegianer}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|oileanach}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|сту̀дент|m}}, {{tt|sh|сту̀дентица|f}} {{qualifier|Croatia, Bosnia}}, {{tt|sh|сту̀денткиња|f}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|stùdent|m}}, {{tt+|sh|stùdentica|f}} {{qualifier|Croatia, Bosnia}}, {{tt|sh|stùdentkinja|f}}\n* Sindhi: {{t-needed|sd}}\n* Sinhalese: {{tt|si|ශිෂ්යයා}}\n* Slovak: {{tt+|sk|študent|m}}, {{tt+|sk|študentka|f}}\n* Slovene: {{tt+|sl|študent|m}}, {{tt|sl|študentka|f}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{tt|dsb|student|m}}, {{tt|dsb|studentka|f}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|estudiante|m|f}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|mwanafunzi|1/2}}, {{tt+|sw|mwanachuo|1/2}}, {{tt+|sw|mwanagenzi|1/2}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|student|c}}, {{tt+|sv|studentska|c}} {{q|female}}, {{tt+|sv|elev|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt+|tl|estudyante}}, {{tt|tl|mag-aaral}}\n* Tajik: {{tt+|tg|донишҷӯ}}, {{tt+|tg|шогирд}}, {{tt+|tg|студент}}, {{t|tg|толиби илм}} {{qualifier|lofty}}\n* Tamil: {{tt+|ta|கற்பவன்}}\n* Tatar: {{tt|tt|студент}}\n* Telugu: {{tt+|te|విద్యార్థి|m}}\n* Thai: {{tt+|th|นักเรียน}}\n* Tibetan: {{tt|bo|སློབ་མ}}, {{tt|bo|སློབ་ཕྲུག}}, {{tt|bo|སློབ་གཉེར་བ}}\n* Tigrinya: {{tt|ti|ተመሃራይ|?}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|öğrenci}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{tt|ota|تلمیذ|tr=tilmiz}}, {{tt|ota|طالب|tr=talib}}, {{tt|ota|درسخوان|tr=darshuan}}, {{t|ota|شاگرد|tr=şagird}}\n* Turkmen: {{tt|tk|student}}, {{tt|tk|talyp}}, {{tt|tk|okuwçy}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|студе́нт|m}}, {{tt|uk|студе́нтка|f}}\n* Urdu: {{tt|ur|طالِبِ عِلْم|m}}, {{tt|ur|چھاتْر|m|f}}, {{tt|ur|طالِب|m}}, {{t|ur|اِسْٹُوڈینْٹ|m}}, {{t|ur|اِسْٹُوڈِنْٹ|m}}, {{t|ur|مُرِید|m}}, {{t|ur|دانِش جُو|m}}, {{t|ur|دانِش آموز|m}}, {{t|ur|شاگِرْد|m}}, {{t|ur|طالِبَہ|f}}, {{t|ur|تِلْمِیذ|m}}, {{t|ur|دَرْس خواں|m}}\n* Uyghur: {{tt|ug|ئوقوغۇچى}}, {{tt|ug|ئىستودېنت}}, {{tt|ug|ستودېنت}}, {{tt|ug|تالىپ}}\n* Uzbek: {{tt+|uz|student}}, {{tt+|uz|talaba|m}}, {{tt+|uz|oʻquvchi|alt=o'quvchi}}, {{tt|uz|tolibi ilm}} {{qualifier|lofty}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|học sinh}} ({{tt|vi|學生}}), {{tt+|vi|sinh viên}} ({{tt|vi|生員}})\n* Volapük: {{tt+|vo|studan}} {{q|♂♀}}, {{tt|vo|histudan}} {{q|♂}}, {{tt|vo|jistudan}} {{q|♀}}, {{tt|vo|studanef}} {{q|collective ♂♀}}, {{tt|vo|histudanef}} {{q|collective ♂}}, {{tt|vo|jistudanef}} {{q|collective ♀}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|myfyriwr|m}}, {{tt|cy|myfyrwraig|f}}\n* Wutunhua: {{tt|wuh|lhoma}}\n* Yiddish: {{tt|yi|סטודענט|m}}, {{tt|yi|תּלמיד|m|tr=talmid}}\n* Yoruba: {{tt|yo|akẹ́kọ̀ọ́}}\n* Yucatec Maya: {{t|yua|xoknáal}}\n* Zazaki: {{tt|zza|taleb}}, {{tt|zza|musayer|c}}, {{tt+|zza|musayoğ}}, {{tt+|zza|musayoğ|c}}\n* Zhuang: {{tt|za|lwghag}}, {{tt|za|hagseng}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|person enrolled at a school, university or other education institution}}\n* Arabic: {{tt+|ar|طَالِب|m}}, {{tt|ar|طَالِبَة|f}}, {{tt|ar|تِلْمِيذ|m}}, {{tt|ar|تِلْمِيذَة|f}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{tt|arz|طالب|m|tr=ṭāleb}}, {{tt|arz|طالبة|f|tr=ṭāleba}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|учени́к|m}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|alumne|m}}, {{tt+|ca|estudiant|m|f}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|lernanto}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|opiskelija}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Lernender|m}}, {{tt+|de|Lernende|f}} {{q|only used as an umbrella term}}\n* Hindi: {{tt+|hi|विद्यार्थी|m}}, {{tt|hi|विद्यार्थिनी|f}}, {{tt+|hi|छात्र|m}}, {{tt+|hi|छात्रा|f}}, {{tt+|hi|शिष्य|m}}, {{tt+|hi|शिष्या|f}}, {{tt+|hi|तालिब|m}}, {{tt+|hi|तालिबा|f}}\n* Irish: {{tt|ga|dalta|m}}\n* Persian:\n*: Iranian Persian: {{tt|fa-ira|دانِشْجو}}, {{tt|fa-ira|دانِش‌آموز}} {{qualifier|for school}}, {{tt|fa-ira|شاگِرْد}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|uczeń|m}}, {{t+|pl|uczennica|f}}\n* Quechua: {{tt|qu|yachachisqa}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|уча́щийся|m}} {{qualifier|umbrella term}}, {{t+|ru|уча́щаяся|f}} {{qualifier|umbrella term}}, {{t+|ru|учени́к|m}} {{qualifier|at a school}}, {{t+|ru|учени́ца|f}} {{qualifier|at a school}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|alumno|m}}, {{tt+|es|estudiante|m|f}}, {{tt+|es|discente|m}}, {{tt+|es|educando|m|f}}\n* Sylheti: {{tt|syl|ꠍꠣꠔ꠆ꠞ}}\n* Tajik: {{tt+|tg|шогирд}}\n* Yoruba: {{tt|yo|akẹ́kọ̀ọ́}}\n* Yucatec Maya: {{t|yua|xoknáal}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top-also|person enrolled at a university|university student}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|nxënës|m}}\n* Arabic: {{tt+|ar|طَالِب|m}}, {{tt|ar|طَالِبَة|f}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|ուսանող}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|tələbə}}\n* Basque: {{tt|eu|ikasle}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt|bg|студе́нт|m}}, {{tt|bg|студе́нтка|f}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|alumne|m}}, {{tt+|ca|estudiant|m|f}}, {{tt+|ca|universitari|m}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{tt|yue|學生|tr=hok6 saang1, hok6 sang1}}\n*: Hokkien: {{tt+|nan-hbl|學生|tr=ha̍k-seng}}\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|學生|tr=xuéshēng}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|student|m}}, {{tt+|cs|studentka|f}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|studerende|c}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|student|m}}, {{tt+|nl|studente|f}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|lernanto}}\n* Estonian: {{tt|et|üliõpilane}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|opiskelija}}, {{tt+|fi|ylioppilas}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|étudiant|m}}, {{tt+|fr|étudiante|f}}\n* Georgian: {{tt|ka|სტუდენტი}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Student|m}}, {{tt+|de|Studentin|f}}; {{q|officialese now often}} {{tt+|de|Studierender|m}}, {{tt+|de|Studierende|f}}; {{q|rarely}} {{tt+|de|Hochschüler|m}}, {{tt+|de|Hochschülerin|f}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|φοιτητής|m}}, {{tt+|el|φοιτήτρια|f}}\n* Hawaiian: {{tt|haw|haumāna}}\n* Hiligaynon: {{tt|hil|estudyante}}, {{tt|hil|palatuon}}\n* Hindi: {{tt+|hi|विद्यार्थी|m}}, {{tt|hi|विद्यार्थिनी|f}}, {{tt+|hi|छात्र|m}}, {{tt+|hi|छात्रा|f}}, {{tt+|hi|शिष्य|m}}, {{tt+|hi|शिष्या|f}}, {{tt+|hi|तालिब|m}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|egyetemista}}, {{tt+|hu|főiskolás}}\n* Indonesian: {{tt+|id|mahasiswa|m}}, {{tt+|id|mahasiswi|f}}\n* Irish: {{tt|ga|mac léinn|m}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|studente|m}}, {{tt+|it|studentessa|f}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|学生|tr=がくせい, gakusei}}\n* Kazakh: {{tt|kk|студент}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|학생(學生)}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{tt+|ckb|قوتابی}}, {{tt|ckb|تەلەبە}}\n* Latin: {{tt+|la|discipulus|m}}, {{tt|la|discipula|f}}, {{tt|la|discipulum|n}}, {{tt|la|discens|m|f|n}}, {{tt|la|studens|m|f|n}}\n* Malay: {{tt+|ms|mahasiswa}}\n* Malayalam: {{tt|ml|വിദ്യാര്‍ത്ഥി|m}}, {{tt|ml|വിദ്യാര്‍ത്ഥിനി|f}}\n* Nepali: {{tt|ne|विद्यार्थी}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt|nb|student|m}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{tt+|nn|student|m}}\n* Pashto: {{tt+|ps|محصل|m|tr=mohasel}}, {{tt|ps|محصله|f|tr=mohasela}}\n* Persian:\n*: Dari: {{tt|prs|مُحَصِّل}}\n*: Iranian Persian: {{tt|fa-ira|دانِشْجو}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|student|m}}, {{tt+|pl|studentka|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|estudante|m|f}}, {{tt+|pt|académico|m}} {{q|Portugal}}, {{tt|pt|académica|f}} {{q|Portugal}}, {{tt+|pt|acadêmico|m}} {{q|Brazil}}, {{tt+|pt|acadêmica|f}} {{q|Brazil}}, {{tt+|pt|aluno|m}}, {{tt+|pt|aluna|f}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|student|m}}, {{tt+|ro|studentă|f}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|студе́нт|m}}, {{tt+|ru|студе́нтка|f}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{tt|gd|oileanach|m}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{tt|dsb|student|m}}, {{tt|dsb|studentka|f}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|estudiante|m|f}}, {{tt+|es|alumno|m}}, {{tt+|es|alumna|f}}, {{tt+|es|universitario|m}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|mwanafunzi|1/2}}, {{tt+|sw|mwanachuo|1/2}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|student|c}}, {{tt+|sv|studentska|c}} {{q|female}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt+|tl|estudyante}}, {{tt|tl|mag-aaral}}\n* Tajik: {{tt+|tg|донишҷӯ}}\n* Telugu: {{tt+|te|విద్యార్థి|m}}\n* Thai: {{tt+|th|นักศึกษา}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|üniversiteli}}, {{tt+|tr|üniversite öğrencisi}}\n* Urdu: {{tt|ur|طالِبِ عِلْم|m}}, {{tt|ur|چھاتْر|m}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|sinh viên}} ({{tt|vi|生員}})\n* Volapük: {{tt+|vo|studan}} {{q|♂♀}}, {{tt|vo|histudan}} {{q|♂}}, {{tt|vo|jistudan}} {{q|♀}}, {{tt|vo|studanef}} {{q|collective ♂♀}}, {{tt|vo|histudanef}} {{q|collective ♂}}, {{tt|vo|jistudanef}} {{q|collective ♀}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|myfyriwr|m}}, {{tt|cy|myfywraig|f}}\n* Yoruba: {{tt|yo|akẹ́kọ̀ọ́}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-see|schoolchild, pupil, person attending school|schoolchild}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Latin: {{tt+check|la|discipulus|m}}, {{tt-check|la|discipula|f}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt+check|mn|оюутан}}, {{tt+check|mn|сурагч}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{en-adj|-}}\n\n# In [[training]], [[learn]]ing a particular [[skill]].\n#: {{ux|en|'''student''' [[teacher]].}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''student''' [[driver]].}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|en|learner}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=densttu|stunted}}\n\n{{C|en|Education|People}}\n\n==Afrikaans==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|af|nl|student}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|af|LL-Q14196 (afr)-Oesjaar-student.wav}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{af-noun|e}}\n\n# {{l|en|student}}\n\n==Crimean Tatar==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|crh|ru|студент}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{hyph|crh|stu|dent}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|crh|noun}}\n\n# {{l|en|student}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{crh-decl|e|t}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:crh:Luğatçıq}}\n\n==Czech==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{cs-IPA}}\n* {{audio|cs|Cs-student.ogg}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{cs-noun|m-an|f=studentka|adj=studentský}}\n\n# {{l|en|student}} {{gloss|academic, at university}}\n#: {{syn|cs|študák}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{cs-ndecl|m.an}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|cs|studentský}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|cs\n|studentka\n|studium\n|studovna\n|studovat\n}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|cs|žák}}\n* {{l|cs|posluchač}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:cs:PSJC}}\n* {{R:cs:SSJC}}\n* {{R:cs:IJP}}\n\n{{C|cs|Education}}\n\n==Danish==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|da|la|studēns}}, a present participle of {{m|la|studeō|studēre|t=to favour, study}}. Compare also {{cog|en|student}}, {{cog|de|Student}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|da|[sd̥uˈd̥enˀd̥]}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{da-noun|en|er}}\n\n# a person who has [[graduate]]d from {{l|da|gymnasium}}\n# {{l|en|student}} {{q|at a university}}\n#: {{synonyms|da|studerende}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{da-decl|en|er}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:DDO}}\n* {{R:ODS online}}\n\n==Dutch==\n{{wp|nl:}}\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|nl|la|studēns}}, present participle of {{m|la|studeō|studēre|t=to study}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/styˈdɛnt/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-student.ogg}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|stu|dent}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|ɛnt|s=2}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{nl-noun|m|-en|+|f=studente}}\n\n# {{lb|nl|Netherlands}} a {{l|en|student}} at an institute for [[academic]] tertiary education\n# {{lb|nl|Belgium|Suriname}} a {{l|en|student}} at an institute for secondary or tertiary education. {{rfv-sense|nl}}\n<!-- RFV not so much the sense as such, but the alleged regional distinction. Dutch Wikipedia (26.01.2023) explicitly says: \"In België worden personen die hoger onderwijs volgen studenten genoemd. Personen die secundair onderwijs volgen noemt men scholieren of leerlingen.\" -->\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col3|nl\n|geneeskundestudent\n|rechtenstudent\n|spookstudent\n|studentencorps\n|studentenflat\n|studentengroep\n|studentenhuis\n|studentenhuisvesting\n|studentenkamer\n|studentenstad\n|studentenvereniging\n|studentikoos\n}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|nl|studeren}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|pap|student|bor=1}} {{q|dated}}\n\n{{C|nl|Education}}\n\n==Latin==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{la-IPA}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|la|verb form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|la|studeō||3|p|pres|actv|indc}}\n\n==Livonian==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|liv|lv|students}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{liv-p}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|liv|noun}}\n\n# (university/college) [[#English|student]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{liv-decl|140}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:liv:LEL|student}}\n\n==Lower Sorbian==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|dsb|la|studēns}}, present participle of {{m|la|studeō}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{dsb-noun|m-an|f=studentka}}\n\n# {{l|en|student}} {{gloss|person who studies an academic subject; person enrolled at a university}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{dsb-decl-noun-18|studen|t|animate=1}}\n\n{{C|dsb|Education}}\n\n==Naga Pidgin==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|nag|en|student}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|nag|noun|plural|students|or|students khan|or|student khan}}\n\n# {{l|en|student}} {{gl|person enrolled at a school, university or other education institution}}\n\n==Norwegian Bokmål==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|nb|de|Student}}, from {{der|nb|la|studēns}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nb|/stʉˈdɛnt/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{nb-noun-m1}}\n\n# a {{l|en|student}} {{q|at university or college}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|nb|medisinstudent}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:nb:OB}}\n\n==Norwegian Nynorsk==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|nn|de|Student}}, from {{der|nn|la|studēns}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nn|/stʉːdɛnt/}} {{nn-pronu-note}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{nn-noun-m1}}\n\n# a {{l|en|student}} {{q|person enrolled at a university}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|nn|medisinstudent}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:nn:OB}}\n\n==Piedmontese==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|pms|/styˈdɛŋt/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|pms|noun|g=m}}\n\n# {{l|en|student}}\n\n==Polish==\n{{wp|pl:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|pl|:bor|de:Student<ref:{{R:pl:WSWO}} !!! {{R:pl:USJP}}>|etydate=16th century<ref:{{R:pl:SXVI|+|14680}}>|tree=+|text=+}}. Compare {{cog|csb|sztudent}} and {{cog|szl|sztudynt}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pl-pr|a=Pl-#.ogg;LL-Q809 (pol)-Olaf-#.wav|mp=#,[én]}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pl-noun|m-pr|dim=studencik,studenciak|aug=studencina|f=studentka|adj=studencki}}\n\n# {{lb|pl|education}} {{l|en|student}}, [[university student]] {{gl|person who is enrolled at a college or university}}\n#: {{syn|pl|żak}}\n#: {{hyper|pl|uczeń}}\n# {{lb|pl|education|obsolete}} {{l|en|student}}, [[pupil]] {{gl|person who learns at a school}}\n#: {{syn|pl|uczeń}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{pl-decl-noun-m-pr}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|pl|title=adverb|studencko}}\n{{col|pl|title=nouns|studenckość|studenteria}}\n\n===Trivia===\n{{pl-freq 1990|4|44|25|4|3|80|809|567|2}}\n\n===References===\n{{reflist}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pl:WSJP}}\n* {{R:pl:PWN}}\n* {{R:pl:SXVII|STUDENT|16562||01.10.2010}}\n* {{R:pl:SJP1807}}\n* {{R:pl:SJP1861}}\n* {{R:pl:SJP1900||483|6}}\n\n{{C|pl|Male people|Universities}}\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|ro|it|studente}}, {{bor|ro|de|Student}},  {{bor|ro|la|[[studēns|studēns, studentis]]}}.<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20100613145140/https://dexonline.ro/definitie/student student]\" in [https://dexonline.ro/ dexonline]</ref>\n\n===Noun===\n{{ro-noun|m|studenți|f=studentă}}\n\n# [[college]] {{l|en|student}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{ro-noun-m|pl=studenți}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|ro|elev}}\n* {{l|ro|elevă}}\n\n===References===\n<references />\n\n{{C|ro|People}}\n\n==Serbo-Croatian==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|sh|/stǔdent/}}\n* {{hyph|sh|stu|dent}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sh-noun|stùdent|m-an}}\n\n# {{l|en|student}} {{q|usually at a college or university}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{sh-decl-noun\n|stùdent|stùdenti\n|stùdenta|stùdenātā\n|stùdentu|stùdentima\n|stùdenta|stùdente\n|stùdente|stùdenti\n|stùdentu|stùdentima\n|stùdentom|stùdentima\n}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:sh:HJP|d1plWRA%3D}}\n\n==Swedish==\n{{wp|sv:}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|sv|/stɵˈdɛnt/}}\n* {{audio|sv|Sv-student.ogg|a=Gotland|text=en student}}\n* {{rhymes|sv|ɛnt|s=2}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sv-noun|c}}\n\n# a {{l|en|student}} (at a college or university – compare {{m|sv|elev}})\n## an [[undergraduate]]\n# {{lb|sv|before 1968}} a person with a [[gymnasium]] (upper secondary school) [[diploma]]\n# a (recent) [[gymnasium]] [[graduate]]\n#: {{ux|sv|ta '''studenten'''|graduate from gymnasium|lit=take '''the student''' [idiomatic]}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n\"I was his student\" and the like in the general sense is more idiomatically \"Jag var hans {{l|sv|elev}}.\"\n\n====Declension====\n{{sv-infl-noun-c-er}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col3|sv\n|studentexamen\n|studentkår\n|studentmössa\n|studentorkester\n|studentoverall\n|studentsång\n|ta studenten\n}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|sv|elev}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:svenska.se|so}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saol}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saob}}\n\n{{C|sv|Education|People}}\n\n==Tatar==\n\n===Noun===\n{{tt-pos|noun|l}}\n\n# {{l|en|student}}\n#* {{quote-web|tt|date=2006-10-25|author=tt:Mälikä Basıyr|title=tt:Tatar Däwlät Humanitar Pedagogiä Universitetına 130 yıl|work=lw:tt:Azatlıq radiosı|url=https://www.azatliq.org/a/742686.html|passage=Tatarstannıñ mäğärif ministrı bulıp eşlägän Faris Xarisov, şuşı universitetnı tämamlağan '''student''' ikän.}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{tt-latin-noun|nıñ|qa|nı|ta|tan}}\n\n{{topics|tt|People|Education}}"}}